California, Connecticut, Delaware, Illinois, Iowa, Maine, Massachusetts, Minnesota, New Mexico, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont, Washington and Washington, D.C. joined New York.
Ground-level ozone occurs when common pollutants emitted by cars, power plants, oil refineries, chemical power plants, and other sources react in the atmosphere with solar radiation.
