Four years ago, 10,000 Czech citizens voted for MPs abroad.
"Since the last amendment to the decree in 2013, there have been some changes that need to be taken into account in these lists," the ministry said in a statement.
"In some countries, new representative offices have been created, some offices have been closed, or there has been a change in the level of representation," the report said.
