The latest results of tests to determine the age limit for asylum applications in Sweden
The latest results of tests of asylum seekers in Sweden, who have been subjected to a new method assessing their age, show that over 80 percent of people have been interviewed as older than 18, but not everyone believes their accuracy.
The Swedish Forensic Medical Agency (R<0xC3><0x83><0xC2><0xA4>ttsmedicinalverket) started conducting new tests at the beginning of this year.
