To date, the Swedish Migration Agency has submitted 6,880 cases to the investigation, and the Forensic Medical Agency has now published the results of a total of 2,481 tests conducted from mid-March to July 31, 2017.
Eighty percent (2002) were judged to be older than 18 years, while in another 25 cases the Forensic Medical Agency considered that the respondent was “possibly older than 18 years”.
In another 423 cases, it was decided that the respondent was “possibly under 18 years of age”.
The tests are only applied if the age of the person in question is disputed.
