A one-room apartment with a complicated layout - to get into the bedroom, you had to walk through the kitchen - Joanne wanted to add storage space and mezzanine to take advantage of the high ceiling.
"I longed for a high ceiling, large windows and lots of light.
Those were my demands," she said.
To this end, she employed Erfan Azadi of Duck & Shed, a design and design studio based in Notting Hill, and used a nearly four-foot ceiling to create a home that was not just a project, but also a place to live.
