Erfan had to engage his creative thinking.
"The steel structure is quite complicated," he explained.
“We had to arrange both spaces so that we could walk upright.
It wasn’t just about building a simple platform, but at the same time bending the steel structure so that it was at the right height above and below the ceiling.”
This arrangement allowed Erfan to construct two full-fledged rooms on top of each other - while adding to the drama.
The mezzanine overlooks the beautiful living room of an old copper window frame in Retrouvius design.
Mirror furniture in gold color, silver line and retro chandelier Serge Mouille create a unique style.
