However, what is unique about this solution is the folding door.
"We had to solve the technical side," Erfan says of the reinforced veneered doors.
"The door is equipped with counterweights so that it can be removed very easily."
Thanks to the clever use of space and storage spaces, Joanne gained another 16 square meters, a second room and a better overall layout of the apartment.
"When it comes down to it, what you're selling is living space -- or the valuation of your property," Erfan said.
"A real estate agent basically calculates when entering an apartment his price based on the living area."
In this case, it was possible to increase the living area while maintaining quality materials that give the space a luxurious appearance.
“The material is very important because you touch it and create an emotional bond with your home,” Erfan added.
“You don’t love the electricity distribution in the walls.
Yes, they are important, but your heart will not win.”
As it turned out, high-quality design and an increase in living space can turn an ordinary apartment into an exceptional work.
And just like Joanne, you can finally decide to stay.
