Trade unions are demanding assurances from McVitie's cookie makers about a long-term manufacturing commitment at a Glasgow factory.
The Scottish trade union GMB said the company was silent on any investment in the Tollcross plant for the time being.
The factory has more than 500 employees who produce, among other products, cookies Hobnob and Rich Tea.
